1. What is the minimum Aerial drop height over a road?
a. 15 ½ ft



2. What is the minimum Aerial drop height over a Driveway?
a. 11 ½ ft



3. What is the minimum Aerial drop height over a pedestrian walk way (deck, yard, side walk)?
a. 9 ½ ft



4. What is the aerial separation from power at the Pole?
a. 40 inches



5. What is the aerial separation from Telephone or another utility at the Pole?
a. 12 inches



6. How far must a P-hook be from Power's attachment on a house?
a. 12 inches



7. How far must a P-hook be from Telephone or another utility's attachment on a house?
a. 6 inches



8. How far must a Q-clamp (span clamp) be from the center of the Pole?
a. 30 inches



9. How far must a Q-clamp (span clamp) be from any hardline devices (Tap, Splitter, Amplifier...)?
a. 6 inches



10. What is the maximum Vertical (up to down) attachment spacing of a cable (coax, ground wire, phone outlet)?
a. 36 inches



11. What is the minimum Horizontal (left to right) attachment spacing of a cable (coax, ground wire, phone outlet)?
a. 12-18 inches



12. What is the height requirement for any newly installed housebox?
a. 3-5 ft



13. What is the "Do Not Enter" zone (no holes or houseboxes) of a power meter?
a. From the ground to 6 ft above the power meter



14. What is the Maximum length of a ground wire/bond wire?
a. 20ft



15. Where does a bond tag get placed?
a. Within 2 inches of the bond point



16. How many bond tags are installed when bonding on the interior?
a. 2, and written location of bond in housebox



17. What is the hierarchy of bonding attachment locations?
a. IBT (Intersystem Bonding Terminal/Termination) (Inside or outside)
b. #6 Ground wire (Inside or outside)
c. Power Meter Enclosure and or the Power Mast (Metal only)
d. Steel frame of a building/Mobile home



18. What is the minimum distance from an electrical outlet that a Coax can be installed?
a. 6 inch separation



19. How many splices can an existing Aerial drop have in it?
a. 0



20. How many splices can an existing Underground drop have in it?
a. 2



21. How many splices can an existing outlet have in it?
a. 1



22. Follow power
22. Follow power



23. What is the maximum length of excess coax within a Pedestal?
a. No more than 12 inches above the top of the pedestal



24. What devices can all be used to secure a housebox shut?
a. Zip-tie, plastic lock, orange tag



25. At what point in the wiring must a bond be made before?
a. Before the first device (splitter)



26. When placing an underground drop, the pedestal must be secured shut with what?
a. Metal lock, plastic lock, P-Key, star lock



27. When placing a temp underground drop, the drop must enter the pedestal in what manner to allow the pedestal to be secured shut?
a. Digging the drop in, using a knock-out, drilling into a Plastic pedestal at ground level (never metal ped)



28. The temp drop must be picked up and put into your vehicle if the customer has what type of order?
a. Disconnect or non-pay disconnect



29. All entry holes must be ________ no matter the size of the hole.
a. Sealed or filled



30. All conduit must be _______ after visiting the ped or pole.
a. Sealed with a conduit cap or filled with putty



31. Zip-ties should be pulled only tight enough for the ________ to be able to be slide back and forth through it.
a. Coax, ground wire, phone cable



32. Excess tags on a drop are considered what?
a. Trash



33. A Zip-tie should be placed how far below the tap in a pedestal, to prevent the orange tag from resting in the dirt?
a. 6 inches or just so the tag doesn't rest in the dirt



34. All coaxial cable used by Midco is what Ohm?
a. 75 Ohm



35. All Tap ports must have a _________ on each unused port, and check for tightness.
a. 75 Ohm locking Terminator



36. All F-connectors must be a ____________ style connector, or be replaced with one?
a. Compression connector



37. All __________ entering the earth require conduit or equivalent protection from rodent, weed-whip...damage.
a. Coax, drop, outlets



38. A steel sided house requires the use of what style siding clip?
a. Steel siding clip



39. A vinyl sided house requires the use of what style siding clip?
a. Vinyl siding clip



40. A wood, brick, mason... sided house may use of what style siding clip?
a. Screw clip, flex clip, anchor if brick/block/mortar



41. When drilling a hole you should always drill at what angle from the Inside to outside?
a. Slightly downward



42. Leaving zip-ties uncut on a housebox, coax, attachment point is considered _________.
a. Trash



43. What specifications must a splitter have to be acceptable to use?
a. Welded back plate, 5-1,000 MHz



44. What specifications must an Amplifier have to be acceptable to use?
a. 5-1,000 MHz



45. What is the minimum and maximum signal level input to an amplifier?
a. 0 dB min and 12 dB max on a digital channel



46. What is the Forward minimum to maximum signal level to a STB?
a. -6 dB to +12 dB



47. What is the Forward minimum to maximum signal level to a DOCSIS device?
a. -10 dB to +10 dB



48. Define what devices are "DOCSIS"?
a. Modems, EMTA



49. What is the Return minimum to maximum signal level to both a STB & a DOCSIS device?
a. 35 to 52 dB



50. What is the minimum MER?
a. 33dB



51. What is the Minimum BER?
a. 1.0e-9



52. What does that 1.0.E-9 mean?
a. 1 = bits - E = errors - 9= number of zeros behind the 1.



53. What is the minimum Upstream SNR?
a. 28 dB



54. What is the minimum In-Band SNR - On a STB's Diagnostic Screen?
a. 33 dB



55. What is the minimum Out-of-Band SNR - On a STB's Diagnostic Screen?
a. 20 dB



56. What is the remote login credentials for all Midco modems?
a. admin - cableroot



57. What buttons are pressed to Format (Wipe) a Motorola's Hard Drive?
a. Quick rewind once, List twice, Live once



58. What is the Toll free phone number to Midco?
a. 1-800-888-1300



59. What must be in the comments on every drop bury form?
a. Tech's name and phone number



60. When must a person's "Out of Office" be enabled?
a. Any normally scheduled work day that a tech might have worked



61. What is the loss of a 2 way splitter?
a. 3.5 dB



62. What is the loss of a 4 way splitter?
a. 7 dB



63. What is the loss of an 8 way splitter?
a. 11 dB



64. What is the loss of a 6 way splitter?
a. 9 dB



65. What is the loss of a balanced 3 way splitter?
a. 5.5 dB



66. What is the loss of an unbalanced 3 way splitter?
a. 3.5, 7 & 7 dB



67. What is the through loss of a DC6?
a. 2 - 2.2 dB



68. What is the tap loss of a DC6?
a. 6 dB



69. What is the loss on channel 134 or 860 MHz on RG-6 coax over 100 feet?
a. About 6 db



70. What is the loss on channel 116 or 750 MHz on RG-6 coax over 100 feet?
a. 5.5 db



71. What is the loss on channel 78 or 550 MHz on RG-6 coax over 100 feet?
a. 4.5 dB



72. What is the loss on channel 2 or 5 MHz on RG-6 coax over 100 feet?
a. 1.5 dB



73. What is the loss on the Return or 23-36 MHz on RG-6 coax over 100 feet?
a. 1 dB



74. What is the symbol of a 2 port - 23 value tap on the Ponderosa map?
a. Circle with a 23 in it



75. What is the symbol of a 4 port - 11 value tap on the Ponderosa map?
a. Square with an 11 in it



76. What is the symbol of a 8 port - 17 value tap on the Ponderosa map?
a. Hexagon with a 17 in it



77. What is the symbol of an Amp on the Ponderosa map?
a. Triangle



78. What is the symbol of Fiber on the Ponderosa map?
a. Circle with 2 arrows in it



79. What is the symbol of a 2 way splitter on the Ponderosa map?
a. Circle with the number 2 in it



80. What does a circle with a partial half-moon fill represent on the Ponderosa map?
a. DC



81. How deep should a drop that has been buried in conduit be?
a. 12 inches minimum depth



82. What do you do if you find oxidation on the coax (anywhere, drop, outlet, ground-block...)?
a. Remove the oxidation till good braid/foil are found, or replace the outlet/drop



83. What is the maximum length (cutoff length) of a RG-6 drop?
a. 150 ft



84. What is the maximum length (cutoff length) of RG-11 drop?
a. 250 ft



85. What is the maximum length drop allowed in a Temp situation?
a. As long as the signal level is good enough to work at the CPE or Amplifier



86. What is the zip code for Donlen's fuel card?
a. 60015



87. How often should your oil be changed if your vehicle is 2010 or newer?
a. Every 7,500 miles or when Donlen says to.



88. What type of oil should a 2010 or newer be using?
a. Synthetic oil



89. How often should your oil be changed if your vehicle is older than 2010?
a. Every 5,000 miles



91. Per FTR, where do all orders start, and why?
a. At the Tap, to ensure there isn't a problem with the drop/tap.



92. Use this tool ___ before you come in contact with the Aerial Span, Metal Pedestal, power supply...
a. Foreign Voltage Detector



93. How do you get into the Diagnostics of a HDDTA?
a. Hold down the 0 key, go to Virtual channel map



94. All outlets installed by Midco must be wired in what method (topology), how?
a. Home Run method



95. What Status are you in when working with the Trainer?
a. Training Time



96. What status are you in when working with a Mentor?
a. New Hire Tech - Task Tracker - Enroute, Start



97. What colors are the Tip & Ring for phone service?
a. Green & Red or W/blue & Blue



98. What are the quiet line, 1 kHz tone, phone ID telephone number to dial
a. Xxx-0043
b. Xxx-0042
c. Xxx-0069



99. At what height of a ladder is a hard hat & Eye protection required?
a. 6 ft



100. What frequency is the Return Band?
a. 5-42 MHz



101. What frequency is the Forward Band?
a. 54-860 MHz



102. Self-Terminating Taps are which?
a. 2port 4 value, 4port 8 value, 8port 11 value



103. What is the Out of Band Frequency for Set Top Boxes
a. 75.25 MHz



104. What is the Return frequency of a Set Top Box?
a. 8.096 MHz



105. When drilling a hole, you must always push the cable in, attach the wall plate then go back outside attach to the siding.



106. What buttons do you press to clear the HDDTA remote's codes?
a. Hold Setup till green, then press either 987, 986, 981



107. What buttons do you press to remove RF Pairing on TiVo Remote?
a. Hold TiVo button and Red letter C button



108. How many CLI (leaks) are you required to enter per month/quarter?
a. 6 per month or 18 per quarter



109. How do you identify a new/Prime account number?
a. It ends with a 01



110. How Many outlets get added for free?
a. 2



111. PIC & LPIC
a. 700



112. What is our highest D3.1 QAM Modulation?
a. 4096
